# Artificial-Planeswalker environment template.
#
# The app is a stateless MCP server (src/mcp_server), consumed by an MCP client such as
# Claude Code or Claude Desktop. The client is the LLM — the server makes NO LLM calls, so
# NO API key is required. Every setting below has a sensible default, so copying this file to
# .env is optional (the server reads these from the real environment, not from .env directly).

# --- Data location -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# By default the card DB and the fastembed model cache live in a shared, OS-appropriate data
# directory, so every MCP client on this machine reuses one ~250 MB dataset:
#   Windows: %LOCALAPPDATA%\artificial-planeswalker
#   macOS:   ~/Library/Application Support/artificial-planeswalker
#   Linux:   ~/.local/share/artificial-planeswalker   (honours XDG_DATA_HOME)
# Override the whole location with:
# PLANESWALKER_DATA_DIR=/path/to/shared/data

# Explicit database URL — overrides PLANESWALKER_DATA_DIR for the DB only. Named
# CARDS_DATABASE_URL (not DATABASE_URL) to avoid the Chainlit conflict. Uncomment to pin the DB
# to a specific file, e.g. the old project-relative location:
# CARDS_DATABASE_URL=sqlite+aiosqlite:///./data/cards.db

# fastembed model cache — overrides PLANESWALKER_DATA_DIR for the cache only. Pin it to a
# PERSISTENT path; never fastembed's volatile %TEMP%\fastembed_cache default.
# FASTEMBED_CACHE_DIR=/path/to/fastembed_cache

# --- MCP transport -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Read by src/mcp_server. Default: stdio (how MCP clients launch it). Override to "sse" or
# "streamable-http" to serve over HTTP instead.
MCP_TRANSPORT=stdio

# --- Scryfall import (chosen via a CLI flag, not an env var) -----------------------------
#   uv run python scripts/import_scryfall_data.py --type oracle_cards
# oracle_cards  (~30k cards, 79MB, 2-3 min)  — one canonical card per Oracle ID.
# default_cards (~60k cards, 200MB, 6-9 min) — all printings; accurate Arena/MTGO games filter.
